#### 1.2 Fix ESC Key Priority Logic (5 min)

**File:** `src/hooks/useEscapeKey.ts`

**Current Code (Lines 26-35):**
```typescript
const handleEscape = (e: KeyboardEvent) => {
  if (e.key === 'Escape') {
    const currentPriority = (e as any)._escPriority || -1;

    if (priority > currentPriority) {  // ❌ Wrong comparison
      (e as any)._escPriority = priority;
      e.stopPropagation();
      e.preventDefault();
      onEscape();
    }
  }
};
```

**Fix:**
```typescript
const handleEscape = (e: KeyboardEvent) => {
  if (e.key === 'Escape') {
    const currentPriority = (e as any)._escPriority || -1;

    if (priority >= currentPriority) {  // ✅ Higher or equal priority wins
      (e as any)._escPriority = priority;
      e.stopPropagation();
      e.preventDefault();
      onEscape();
    }
  }
};
```

**Explanation:**
- Modal (priority 9999) should execute FIRST
- AI Terminal (priority 40) should NOT execute when modal already handled it
- `>=` ensures higher priority always wins, ties go to first handler

